This project analyzes the performance of TradeZone, a fast-growing Nigerian e-commerce platform operating across major cities including Lagos, Abuja, Kano, Port Harcourt, and Ibadan.

The goal of this analysis is not just to report metrics, but to understand what is actually happening in the business and translate data into clear decisions for leadership.

The project focuses on three key areas:

Customer acquisition and conversion performance
Product and category performance distribution
Customer spending behaviour and revenue concentration

All analysis was done using PostgreSQL, supported by structured data cleaning, validation checks, and business-focused SQL queries.

🧠 Business Problem

Despite rapid platform growth, TradeZone is facing three hidden structural issues:

Weak conversion of new users into paying customers
Heavy reliance on a small number of high-value customers
Uneven product category performance despite marketing investment

The Head of Growth and Head of Seller Operations requested an analysis that goes beyond dashboards and focuses on business decisions.
